refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public boolImagick::blackThresholdImage mixedthreshold
Is like Imagick::thresholdImage() but forces all pixels below the threshold into black while leaving all pixels above the threshold unchanged.

&reftitle.parameters;




   threshold



     The threshold below which everything turns black

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     PECL imagick 2.1.0

      Now allows a string representing the color as a parameter.
      Previous versions allow only an ImagickPixel object.

  &reftitle.examples;



       Imagick::blackThresholdImage


<?php
function blackThresholdImage($imagePath, $thresholdColor) {
    $imagick = new \Imagick(realpath($imagePath));
    $imagick->blackthresholdimage($thresholdColor);
    header("Content-Type: image/jpg");
    echo $imagick->getImageBlob();
}

?>
